(4. Installing Demos Commander) 11 P
(To install the Demos Commander Package, use the following) 13 P
(procedure:) 14 P
(    *  Log in to the system as root.) 16 P
(    *  Create temporary directory, then enter it:) 18 P
(            mkdir /tmp/deco) 20 P
(            cd /tmp/deco) 21 P
(    *  Insert the Demos Commander diskette into drive 0.) 23 P
(    *  Read distribution into current directory:) 25 P
(            tar xvbf 18 /dev/rfd048ds9) 27 P
(    *  Run installation script:) 29 P
(            ./INSTALL) 31 P
(    *  After completion of the installation remove the temporary) 33 P
(       directory:) 34 P
(            cd /tmp) 36 P
(            rm -r deco) 37 P
(To remove Demos Commander, use script /usr/lib/deco/UNINSTALL.) 39 P
(Running Demos Commander on Xenix console you may use terminal) 41 P
(types 'ansi' or 'xenix'. In fact, Terminal type 'ansi' is not) 42 P
(true ansi description, but is adjusted to Xenix console.) 43 P
(If you are running real ansi device, you must use TERM=trueansi.) 44 P
(To setup terminal type, use:) 46 P
(    $ TERM=termtype) 48 P
(    $ export TERM) 49 P
(in shell, or) 51 P
(    \45 setenv TERM termtype) 53 P
