(5. Adding a new terminal type.) 3 P
(Demos Commander handles a terminal using a terminal capability) 5 P
(database termcap. Commander has its own termcap appendix) 6 P
(/usr/lib/deco/termcap, which is read before standard) 7 P
(/etc/termcap. Indirections tc=name in deco's own termcap refer) 8 P
(to the entry 'name' in the default terminal database. You can) 9 P
(use your own terminal database instead of the default) 10 P
(/etc/termcap. To do this, set the global variable TERMCAP to) 11 P
(the full name of your file \(for example,) 12 P
(TERMCAP=/usr/my/termcap\).) 13 P
